I think I understand the direction better now.

You’re no longer talking only about cognition. You’re asking whether modulation itself could become the computational interface, with memory represented as changes (deltas) rather than static values.

There are a few ideas here that already have analogs in computing, and then there’s your proposed synthesis.

1. Delta-based memory

Instead of storing complete states:

S0
S1
S2
S3

store only the changes:

S0
Δ1
Δ2
Δ3

That’s a well-established idea in several contexts (version control, video compression, event sourcing, differential backups), because changes are often much smaller than complete copies.

